[SN]TITLE[SN]
Man dies following motorbike and car crash on A947 in Aberdeenshire

[SN]FIRST-SENTENCE[SN]
A man has died following a crash involving a motorbike and a car in Aberdeenshire.

[SN]RESTBODY[SN]
Police said the victim was in his 50s.
Emergency services attended the scene of the collision on the A947 Aberdeen to Banff road at Plaidy at 07:44. A black Victory motorcylce and a grey Audi A1 were involved.
The road is expected to be closed for some time to allow for investigation work into the collision. Drivers have been advised to avoid the area.
Road Policing Inspector Ewan Innes said: "Both vehicles were travelling south on the A947 and we are appealing for anyone who may have seen the vehicles prior to the collision to speak to us.
"Our thoughts are with the family and friends of the man who has died and a full collision investigation will be carried out to establish the circumstances."
Traffic diversions are in place. Traffic for Macduff is being redirected along the B9105 and on to the A98. For Banff, traffic is being diverted to the B9025 on to the A97.
